name: Lewis County Mall
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
********This is a single dose Johnson & Johnson and 1ST DOSE PFIZER vaccine clinic.**** and is by appointment or walk-in. Please note: J&J vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements while Pfizer can be administered to those 16 and 17 years of age with signed parental consent.

This clinic is located at the west end of the Lewis County Mall in the former Sears location. Please park in front or to the west end of the building. This is a walk in location. Please let us know if you or someone you are with needs assistance of any kind.  **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation.

Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided.

Please bring your appointment confirmation. Please do not come if you are feeling ill. Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing. - It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. Given the limited supply of COVID-19 vaccine available at this time and Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location must either live or work in Washington state. If you do not live or work in Washington, please do not make an appointment or travel to this site.  **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Arlington Airport Covid-19 Vaccine Site
info:
Everyone 16 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 16 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form).

Appointments are highly recommended but not required.  Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
info:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. *** All patients 16 years old and older can register regardless of phase. (If 16-17 years old must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only. 
***You MUST bring proof that you live or work in WA (such as a utility bill; a voucher from your employer; or your work, school, or state ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Benton Franklin - Kennewick COVID Vaccine Clinic
info: ******Pfizer Clinic***** All patients 16 years old and older can register. If you are 16-17 years old you must be with a parent or guardian or verbal parental/guardian consent. **FOR 2ND DOSE PLEASE BRING YOUR COVID-19 VACCINATION RECORD CARD** For Both 1st and 2nd dose - Please bring your appointment confirmation. Given the limited supply of COVID-19 vaccine available at this time and Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location you must either live or work in Washington state. name: Community Vaccination Center at Bellingham Technical College
address: Bellingham Technical College, 3028 Lindbergh Avenue – Building G, Bellingham WA, 98225
info: We are currently vaccinating eligible individuals as determined by Washington State Department of Health ages 18 and older.  If appointments are full, you can click on “Waiting List” to register yourself for standby appointments for that scheduling day only.  If there are extra doses of vaccine at the end of the day, individuals on the waiting list will be called in scheduling order.  You can also make an appointment by calling 360-778-6075 Monday through Friday from 8:30 AM to 4:00 PM.  Phone appointments are available for people who do not have an email, internet access, need interpretation services, or are having difficulty navigating the site.  On-site registration is available as well. Masks must be worn at all times at the site and six-foot distancing will be maintained.  The site is ADA accessible.  For directions, visit www.vaccinatewhatcom.org.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
